---
description: Project context and lessons-learned workflow
globs: "*"
---

- Before major architecture, debugging, or planning work, read `MEMORY.md` if it exists.
- Before changing project-specific architecture, workflow, or plans, read `.cursor/project-context/`. If it enables Chinese-native Python docs, apply `bilingual-comments.mdc`.
- When debugging, fixing CI failures, or retrying after repeated failures, read `.cursor/lessons-learned/`.
- After major decisions, deep bug fixes, or repeated-failure resolutions, proactively suggest a concise memory update.
- Store project-specific state in `.cursor/project-context/`; store reusable bug lessons in `.cursor/lessons-learned/`.
- Keep notes short, clear, and easy for agents to scan. Prefer bullets over long prose.
- Never store secrets, credentials, private tokens, or long transcripts in these files.
- Write project memory in English unless the project explicitly chooses another language.
